<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
1. Pygidium strongly convex. Metasternal anterior lobe convex or flat (
<figureCitation box="[1110,1187,896,922]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="4.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[300,1304,283,1834]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[264,1324,265,1858]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig. 1. A–C, G–H. Canthon (G.) smaragdulus smaragdulus (Fabricius, 1781). – D–F, I–J. Canthon (G.) fulgidus fulgidus Redtenbacher, 1868. A, D. Ventral surface of meso- and metafemora. B, E. Metasternal anterior lobe convex. C, F. Dorsal view showing convex pygidium. G, I. Paramera lateral view. H, J. Paramera dorsal view. Scale bar: 2.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3787889" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3787889/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Dorsal surface glabrous with blue, green, golden, or red metallic sheen (
<figureCitation box="[919,1029,932,958]" captionStart-0="Fig" captionStart-1="Fig" captionStart-2="Fig" captionStartId-0="7.[189,232,1930,1956]" captionStartId-1="12.[189,232,1932,1958]" captionStartId-2="19.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox-0="[201,1366,761,1893]" captionTargetBox-1="[253,1337,488,1890]" captionTargetBox-2="[202,1379,264,1882]" captionTargetId-0="figure@7.[197,1391,751,1893]" captionTargetId-1="figure@12.[236,1352,478,1899]" captionTargetId-2="figure@19.[189,1399,263,1882]" captionTargetPageId-0="7" captionTargetPageId-1="12" captionTargetPageId-2="19" captionText-0="Fig. 2. A. Canthon (G.) smaragdulus smaragdulus (Fabricius, 1781). – B–D. C. (G.) smaragdulus subviridis Schmidt, 1922 stat. rev. A–B. Habitus. C. Male protibial spur. D. Female protibial spur. Scale bar: A–B = 5.0 mm." captionText-1="Fig. 3. A. Canthon (G.) fulgidus fulgidus Redtenbacher, 1868. B. C. (G.) fulgidus martinezi subsp. nov. C–E. C. (G.) fulgidus pereirai subsp. nov. D. Male protibial spur. E. Female protibial spur. Scale bar: A–C = 5.0 mm." captionText-2="Fig. 4. Canthon (G.) bicolor Castelnau, 1840. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Ventral surface of meso- and metafemora and metasternal anterior lobe not convex. C. Dorsal view showing convex pygidium. D. Male protibial spur. E. Female protibial spur. F. Paramera lateral view. G. Paramera dorsal view. Scale bar: A = 5.0 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3787891" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3787893" figureDoi-2="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3787895" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/3787891/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/3787893/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/3787895/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Figs 2–4</figureCitation>
). Ventral surface of metafemur not marginate anteriorly …………………2 
<taxonomicName authority="Pereira" authorityName="Pereira" authorityYear="1956" box="[766,1399,968,995]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Goniocanthon">
