</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,896,1139]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
– Pygidium flat or slightly convex. Metasternal anterior lobe, if protuberant, angled or truncated, not convex. Dorsal surface pubescent or glabrous, with or without metallic sheen. Ventral surface of metafemur marginate or not anteriorly ……………………………………………………………… ……other subgenera and isolated species-groups of 
<taxonomicName authority="sensu Halffter &amp; Martinez (1977)" authorityName="sensu Halffter &amp; Martinez" authorityYear="1977" box="[872,1399,1112,1139]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Canthon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
