<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1178,1349]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">2. Both pygidium and metasternal anterior lobe strongly convex. Profemur with a tooth on its anterior lower border. Pronotum and elytra with similar colour. South America ……………3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[189,1399,1178,1349]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
– Only pygidium convex (
<figureCitation box="[543,643,1250,1276]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[202,1379,264,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[189,1399,263,1882]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 4. Canthon (G.) bicolor Castelnau, 1840. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Ventral surface of meso- and metafemora and metasternal anterior lobe not convex. C. Dorsal view showing convex pygidium. D. Male protibial spur. E. Female protibial spur. F. Paramera lateral view. G. Paramera dorsal view. Scale bar: A = 5.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3787895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3787895/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). Metasternal anterior lobe flat (
<figureCitation box="[1055,1155,1250,1276]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[202,1379,264,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[189,1399,263,1882]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 4. Canthon (G.) bicolor Castelnau, 1840. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Ventral surface of meso- and metafemora and metasternal anterior lobe not convex. C. Dorsal view showing convex pygidium. D. Male protibial spur. E. Female protibial spur. F. Paramera lateral view. G. Paramera dorsal view. Scale bar: A = 5.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3787895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3787895/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Profemur without tooth on its anterior border (
<figureCitation box="[576,671,1286,1313]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[202,1379,264,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[189,1399,263,1882]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 4. Canthon (G.) bicolor Castelnau, 1840. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Ventral surface of meso- and metafemora and metasternal anterior lobe not convex. C. Dorsal view showing convex pygidium. D. Male protibial spur. E. Female protibial spur. F. Paramera lateral view. G. Paramera dorsal view. Scale bar: A = 5.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3787895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3787895/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
