<figureCitation box="[1288,1386,1286,1313]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="19.[189,232,1894,1920]" captionTargetBox="[202,1379,264,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[189,1399,263,1882]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Fig. 4. Canthon (G.) bicolor Castelnau, 1840. A. Habitus, dorsal view. B. Ventral surface of meso- and metafemora and metasternal anterior lobe not convex. C. Dorsal view showing convex pygidium. D. Male protibial spur. E. Female protibial spur. F. Paramera lateral view. G. Paramera dorsal view. Scale bar: A = 5.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3787895" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3787895/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
). Guyanas, 
<collectingCountry box="[353,468,1322,1348]" name="Suriname" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Suriname</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[481,602,1322,1348]" name="Venezuela" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
…………………………………… 
